    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I don't think there is the equivalent of the <code>{x}</code> syntax for <code>%thread</code>, but you can use something like <code>%.-5thread</code> to print just the first 5 characters of the thread name, but just 5, not a shortened version (obviously, adjust the number to your needs).</p>\n"
